Financial metrics temporarily unavailable (rate limited) - 2025-09-24

Title   : Midcap Mayhem: 11 midcap stocks in freefall, crack 40–50% from peaks. Is your portfolio hit? 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-23T10:05:16
Fetched : 2025-09-24T02:32:13.928920
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/midcap-mayhem-11-midcap-stocks-in-freefall-crack-4050-from-peaks-is-your-portfolio-hit/slideshow/124068151.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Equity markets remain as unpredictable as ever, with sharp swings catching investors off guard. While the benchmark Sensex has dipped 4% and the BSE Midcap Index has fallen 6% from their 52-week highs, several midcap stocks have suffered significantly sharper corrections. Across the BSE Midcap space, nearly 50 stocks have plunged over 25% from their yearly peaks. Among them, 11 names stand out, having crashed 40–50% from their 52-week highs, marking some of the deepest corrections in the segment (Data Source: ACE Equity).
Agencies
2/12
Vedant Fashions has tumbled 50%, currently trading at Rs 750, down from its 52-week high of Rs 1,511
IANS
3/12
Ola Electric Mobility has dropped 49%, with the stock now at Rs 58, compared to its 52-week peak of Rs 113
ETMarkets.com
4/12
Brainbees Solutions has seen a 48% decline, falling to Rs 380 from a high of Rs 734
ETMarkets.com
5/12
Punjab & Sind Bank is down 48%, now priced at Rs 30, significantly below its 52-week high of Rs 58
ETMarkets.com
6/12
Whirlpool of India has corrected 46%, trading at Rs 1,325 from a high of Rs 2,450
Reuters
7/12
Sona BLW Precision Forgings has slipped 45%, with the stock at Rs 421, down from Rs 768
ETMarkets.com
8/12
Relaxo Footwears has declined 44%, currently at Rs 465, compared to its 52-week high of Rs 838
IANS
9/12
Thermax has dropped 43%, falling to Rs 3,272 from its high of Rs 5,721
ETMarkets.com
10/12
UCO Bank has registered a 41% fall, now at Rs 31, from a 52-week high of Rs 52
TNN
11/12
Deepak Nitrite is down 40%, trading at Rs 1,811 against a recent high of Rs 3,012
ETMarkets.com
12/12
Colgate-Palmolive (India) has slipped 40%, with its current price at Rs 2,343, down from Rs 3,893

