Title   : Stocks in news: Mazagon Dock, Swiggy, Tata Motors, Indian Hotels, YES Bank 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-24T00:41:00
Fetched : 2025-09-24T02:52:03.373441
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/stocks-in-news-mazagon-dock-swiggy-tata-motors-indian-hotels-yes-bank/articleshow/124074849.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"Technically, Nifty appears to be consolidating range after three successive weeks of rise. We thus recommend a cautious stance: focus on sectors with relative strength, manage risk carefully, and avoid large directional bets until clearer cues emerge," said Ajit Mishra – SVP, Research, Religare Broking
In today's trade, shares of Mazagon Dock, Swiggy, Tata Motors, Indian Hotels, YES Bank among others will be in focus due to various news developments.
Mazagon Dock
Mazagon Dock Shipbuilders (MDL) announced a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with Guidance Tamil Nadu, the state’s nodal agency for investment to explore the development of a "world-class" greenfield shipyard on India’s eastern coast. The MoU was singed on September 19 between Biju George, Director (Shipbuilding), MDL, and Dr Darez Ahamed, Managing Director & CEO, Guidance Tamil Nadu.
Indian Hotels
Indian Hotels Company Ltd (IHCL) announced the signing of a 310-key Taj hotel in Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh. "We are delighted to continue our partnership with Varun Hospitality Private Limited for this landmark project," IHCL MD and CEO Puneet Chhatwal said in a statement.
YES Bank
Yes Bank said Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corporation (SMBC) of Japan has acquired an additional 4.22% stake in the Mumbai-based bank. With the acquisition, SMBC's stake in Yes Bank has increased from 20% to 24.22%. SMBC has become Yes Bank's largest shareholder, while SBI continues to hold a significant stake of over 10%.
Tata Motors
Tata-owned British luxury carmaker Jaguar Land Rover (JLR) said it has extended the pause in production until Wednesday, 1 October 2025, following a cybersecurity incident that disrupted its operations on September 2.
Puravankara
Deepak Rastogi has resigned as Group CFO and Key Managerial Personnel of the company with effect from the closure of business hours of September 23. Further, Niraj Kumar Gautam has been elevated from the position of Deputy CFO to CFO with effect from September 24 subject to approval of the Members of Nomination and Remuneration Committee.
Swiggy
Food and grocery delivery company Swiggy will sell its 11.8% stake in urban mobility startup Rapido to Prosus and WestBridge Capital for a total of Rs 2,400 crore. Prosus and WestBridge Capital are existing investors in Rapido. The transactions value Rapido at Rs 20,330 crore (or around $2.3 billion), which is a sharp increase from its last valuation of $1.1 billion when it raised funds in 2024.
