Financial metrics temporarily unavailable (rate limited) - 2025-09-24

Title   : JCB India inaugurates its new dealership, KUN Capital Automotive in Tiruchirappalli
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-23T13:40:23
Fetched : 2025-09-24T02:53:35.752121
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/jcb-india-inaugurates-its-new-dealership-kun-capital-automotive-in-tiruchirappalli/article70084887.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JCB India, a leading manufacturer of earthmoving and construction equipment, inaugurated its dealership KUN Capital Automotive in Tiruchirapalli, Tamil Nadu.
With 86 trained sales and service professionals on site, the facility is equipped with six workshop bays, one welding bay, and a Pre-Dispatch Inspection Bay.
Other highlights include a fully operational LiveLink Command Centre for real-time machine monitoring, a Workshop-on-Wheels van, and a dedicated Parts and Service van — ensuring customers receive timely and seamless support, says a release.
Deepak Shetty, CEO and Managing Director - JCB India, said, “Tamil Nadu is India’s second-largest economy and contributes over 8 per cent to the national GDP. It’s a leader in industrialization, with strong manufacturing clusters across automobiles, textiles, and electronics. Also exciting is the state’s forward-looking infrastructure push. In Tiruchirapalli, developments such as the Cauvery Riverfront Project, Trichy International Airport expansion, new ring roads, smart city initiatives under AMRUT, and water body rejuvenation projects are accelerating the demand for reliable earthmoving equipment.”
In addition to this new dealership in Trichy, KUN Capital Automotive has its footprint across Tamil Nadu with seven other strategically located branches in Thanjavur, Karur, Pudukkottai, Ariyalur, Perambalur, Palani, and Dindigul, enhancing accessibility for customers in the region, the release said.
Published on September 23, 2025

