Title   : GMDC, Maruti Suzuki, and 3 other stocks witness 5-year swing high breakout 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-24T02:24:37
Fetched : 2025-09-24T03:02:58.046129
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/gmdc-maruti-suzuki-and-3-other-stocks-witness-5-year-swing-high-breakout/slideshow/124081461.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
In the NSE list of stocks with a market cap over Rs 10,000 crore, five stocks witnessed a 5-year swing high at the close on September 23, suggesting bullishness in counters, according to stockedge.com's technical scan data.
A 5-year swing high represents the highest price a stock has reached within a five-year timeframe. This level acts as a significant resistance point where the price has historically struggled to go beyond. This occurrence may be seen as a bullish sign, indicating the potential for further upward movement in the stock. However, it's worth noting that this is different from a 5-year breakout, which occurs when a stock's price surpasses a key resistance level that has held for five years or longer.

